<title>HONG KONG: CKI's unit forms cement alliance in China.</title>
<headline>CKI's unit forms cement alliance in China.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cheung Kong Infrastructure Holdings Ltd (CKI) said on Sunday its cement business unit had formed a strategic alliance with Guangdong International Trust and Investment Corp (GITIC) to expand cement and concrete business in China.</p>
<p>CKI said in a statement its Green Island Cement (Holdings) Ltd would have a 70 percent stake in the China Cement Company (International) Ltd, which has an asset value of 800 million yuan, while GITIC would take up the remaining 30 percent stake.</p>
</text>
